.TH VSDVIEW 1 "February 2026" "vsdview 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vsdview \- a read-only viewer for Microsoft Visio files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vsdview
.RI [ FILE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vsdview
is a minimal read-only viewer for Microsoft Visio files (.vsdx and .vsd),
built with GTK4 and libadwaita. It uses LibreOffice in headless mode to
convert Visio diagrams to SVG for rendering.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I FILE
An optional Visio file (.vsdx or .vsd) to open on startup.
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.TP
.B Ctrl+O
Open a file
.TP
.B Ctrl+Q
Quit
.TP
.B Ctrl+Plus
Zoom in
.TP
.B Ctrl+Minus
Zoom out
.TP
.B Ctrl+0
Fit to window
.TP
.B F5
Refresh (re-convert current file)
.TP
.B Ctrl+E
Export as PNG
.TP
.B Ctrl+/
Show keyboard shortcuts
.SH DRAG AND DROP
You can drag and drop .vsdx or .vsd files onto the window to open them.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.TP
.B LibreOffice
Required for converting Visio files to SVG. Install via your package manager.
.TP
.B librsvg
Used for SVG rendering.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/vsdview/recent.json
Recently opened files list.
